CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 23, 1960, pg. 3 reads: "Crowd Hears Platform - A crowd of approximately 1,500 persons heard the leaders of the 13th Ward "Rebels" group give details of their platform for the Homewood District Tuesday in Westinghouse High School Auditorium. The rally followed a 1080 car torchlight parade, complete with a brass band.  Intense interest of the audience in what speakers were saying could be seen on many faces in audience."
TitMainTitle: Audience of men and women gathered in Westinghouse High School Auditorium with sign for 9th district to hear leaders of the 13th Ward "Rebels"
